The nicest guy I've ever met and my favorite professor at OSU--favorite teacher I've ever had. You won't find anyone who cares more about their subject and it shows. Always takes time to answer questions and entertain the ideas of every student. Couldn't recommend him highly enough.

Slept through lectures, was barely awake for recitations. still got an A. here's how: BOOKS never read it, go to lectures and wake up for in-class writings, also attend recitation, 3 real easy essays that were max 2 pages. boom you got 50%. 1 mid term and final average 87 on multiple choice exams

Very easy class. However, you need to attend lecture, or you miss information that shows up on tests. Only three homework assignments over the entire semester! And they're simple to do. He sometimes goes off on tangents or loses clarity. He's really goofy, and uses strong hand gestures. However, he's clearly passionate about what he's teaching!

He is the nicest guy in the whole world. He is really energetic and LOVES the subject on which he's teaching. He is passionate about sociology, and as long as you go to class and participate, you'll get a good grade. You have to pay attention, otherwise you might miss some key information because he moves quickly and is a LITTLE confusing.

He has very strong hand gestures. very difficult to follow. He basically turns a very simple concept into more than one whole lecture. Slow on grades, does not email you back AT ALL, and very unorganized. Difficult to succeed

Takes far too long to get grades in, which is inexcusable because his tests are Scantron with short answers. Has very awkward mannerisms that disrupt the flow of his teaching. His chosen subject matter has little relevance considering it's about pre-tweens that know nothing about the significance of sex and religion. Avoid.

Very enthusiastic and never stops moving. He's definitely smart, but too smart for his own good. He sees all sorts of connections between concepts but struggles to explain it to students. He tries to explain things but can't maintain a clear train of thought. Always late to class, but he tries to help outside of class if you can reach him.

Very difficult to understand at times, he uses a vocabulary fit for perhaps graduate school, not a 101 class. Class is mandatory and is graded by little writings at the end of every class. It was painfully difficult to stay awake during his repeated definitions time and time again

He flies through the slides, and doesn't actually explain his computations. He'll put a whole slide of computations and just show you the end result but not actually explain too much of how he got it. I hope you have a prior knowledge of Stats before taking his class.

You don't need the book but you must go to lecture, the online homework is pretty hard but the exams are easy, you get to take a cheat sheet with you to the exams. You also must have the notes for class because he talks way too fast to just write them down. He's a great teacher, the homework, is just difficult.

Witty prof from New Zealand. You don't need to get the book, but you have to go to lecture. Office hours with the TA's saved my life. You have to do online quizzes every week that can be pretty tricky so find a buddy to check answers with! He lets you have an equation sheet but study for exams! I ended up getting an A- and I hate any type of math.
This guy is witty and knows his stuff but should NOT be teaching an intro level class. Flew through slides and the homework is ridiculously hard.

This class is awful. Though he can be entertaining, he cares not about your grade or your comprehension of the material. The homework is outrageously more difficult than the exams. He flies through the material ppts. which are OFTEN riddled with typos, which is very unsettling when trying to learn math.
great teacher

This class was kind of boring. The Prof was funny though and tried to make the material funny and interesting. You don't use the book much (unless you miss lecture) he even tells you not to buy it if you don't want to. His humor adds to his lecture, which is about an hour shorter than the schedule says, but he goes through slides really fast!

He is funny; his New Zealand accent and humor were entertaining. He is willing to help, but has trouble dumbing down the material. Also, he at times gives leeway on hard cut-offs for rejecting the null hypothesis, which is confusing. I highly recommend asking your TA(s) for help if you need it.
AMAZING teacher. He was funny and down to earth. Highly recommended.

homework if anything is what brings down your grade. his midterms are pretty much the EXACT same questions as the ones he presents during the reviews, just write those problems on your cheat sheet and you're pretty much set. easy professor, kind of a mess, DON'T TAKE IT if you don't have to.

Dr.  is AWESOME.The course material is pretty difficult. He moves fast through slides, but fortunately does plenty of examples and always reviews before new stuff is introduced. ASK HIM QUESTIONS! He is really good about explaining stuff. TA's quality varies. Make sure you establish a relationship right away it is beneficial. Lots of HW.

This class is impossible and useless if you do not know anything about statistics. It is supposed to be an introductory class but treats it like an upper-level stats course. He goes through slides too fast and even though they're available through carmen, they're useless if you don't know how to interpret them.

Very boring material and he is really confusing to listen to. If you don't know too much about stats.. he's not going to teach you the basics. He assumes you already know a lot. The material is so dry. He tries to slip some jokes into the lectures.. but it's just painfully boring. Only one of the TA's were helpful, still impossible though.

This class is terrible. , while nice and quirky, does not understand that not everyone understands stats the way he does. I've taken two other stats class and this one, which covered the same stuff, made it impossible. He should not be teaching this low of a class. Plus, the TA's were terrible. Its a good class to have, but not with hi

Professor  was an extremely enjoyable professor who made statistics a much more enjoyable class. He involved himself in the class, and despite initial glitches in the class (CARMEN) maintained a sense of humor. His exams are straight forward IF you pay attention.

psych 320 is harder than regular stats, but prof.  put the notes online, always explained things carefully, and even had a low key quirky sense of humor. he made a boring subject enjoyable and spent plenty of class time working us through problems that would be on the tests - super helpful!!

For being a three credit hour course, he takes it a little too far. Nobody had any idea what would actually be on exam and exam questions were not clearly mentioned on study guide. It was kind of a hopefully I retained this information that he said once during this lecture type deal.

Professor  is passionate about foreign policy but at times comes off as very pretentious during his lectures. He is also a pretty harsh grader, especially with the two memo assignments. There are weekly reading quizzes which aren't bad as long as you read. Some classes will be really interesting and other will be boring, kinda hit or miss.

is a very good lecturer that really tried to make sure you understand the world of international relations and american foreign policy. Very engaging and can be surprisingly funny. His papers are rather difficult however and there is quite a bit of reading and quizzes to do. Does offer Extra Credit. Would highly reccomend

Memos had no guideline and were harshly graded. Lectures could be good but slightly pretentious. Reading quizzes went up day of. Final/midterm were mix of multiple choice and short responses. Course content at times veered away from foreign policy. Would not take again, which is very rare for me.

He only rolls out quizzes 1-2 hours before class starts and those quizzes are due 5 minutes before class starts, because apparently he thinks this is your own only class. The memo assignment is designed for you to fail, he is a very harsh grader on this assignment. The readings are very hard to understand and also boring.

He has readings before every class that were accompanied by difficult reading quizzes. He never sent out rubrics so the papers we had to write were difficult and he is a harsh grader. Worst of all he missed a day of class and got rid of our exam review day in order to go over a pointless lecture at the end of the semester.

Prof.  is extremely passionate about the subject matter AND about his students. Yes, he expects a lot, but there is no way to do badly in his class as long as you genuinely try, go to office hours, and show him that you're improving. He's SO understanding of mental health/personal life stuff and is really helpful if you just ask! He's funny too.

Attendance is semi-mandatory. He grades toughly but is clear is what his expectations are. Reading quizzes are easy and a good way to pad out your grade. Interesting lectures and clearly knows what he is talking about. Readings are not overwhelming.

I loved taking his class in Spring 22. He clearly knows his stuff, he actually cares about his students, he makes his lectures interesting/entertaining, and his assignments are worthwhile. The more you participate, the more you get out of his class. His grades are a little tough, but fair. Plenty of xtra credit opportunities. Take a class with him

Very good intro to foreign policy class- definitely geared towards people with a passion or interest in the subject. His teaching really makes you think about decision making, and you have to push yourself to do well- not an easy class due to the expansive amount of content. Class is mainly reading quizzes, a paper and 2 exams.
Best professor at OSU so far. Truly valuable of class even if you do not have much to do with foreign policy. So much to learn from him and his lectures.

I suffer from general anxiety, and he is probably the most cooperative professor I've ever met when it comes to the matter. He shows a true passion for his subject matter and sharing it with his students

is just an absolute gem of a person. He is so thoughtful, caring and accommodating. I love who he is as a person, despite him being an insanely tough grader. The real issue here is the content. This class is incredibly difficult. There are mountains of readings, slides, and terms that even open note quizzes and tests can't prepare you for.

Foreign policy isn't my strong suit so I knew this class would be a challenge. Takes a good amount of engagement with the material to succeed. Lectures can be dense, note-taking has to be a strong suit. Good prof who cares about his students, just wasn't the most interesting class I've taken. Like foreign policy? Take this. If not, be prepared

I was honestly not expecting this course to be as valuable as it was. Not only does Professor  give you a great base in terms of foreign policy, he teaches you a lot of important skills in terms of writing, formulating your argument, and more. The lectures can definitely be a lot, but its a super rewarding and you truly learn a lot.

One of my favorite professors at OSU. There is a lot of reading, and he is a rather tough grader, but he is also very helpful with feedback. I would say only take this course if you're actually interested in foreign policy. The man is a great lecturer, and if you care about this stuff, you're going to get a lot out of this class.

Professor  is one of the best instructors I have had so far throughout my college career. He is a very tough grader but it made me think significantly more about the content of the class, as opposed to someone who just gave completion credit or graded with minimal effort. He obviously cares about his students' lives in and out of the classroom.

Professor  is an amazing lecturer and gives great feedback. Some people have been saying that he comes off as arrogant or condescending, but I did not get that impression at all. He just expects a lot from his students and encourages them to think through difficult concepts. The class is very reading-heavy and attending the lectures is crucial.

Go to office hours! He is a professor who will respect/help you more if you show him you care about your grade and his class. Don't hesitate to ask for help before memos/midterm/finals. Really knowledgeable and cares about foreign policy issues today. History heavy. For poly sci majors, this class will be a great foundation for future classes.

He's very passionate and clearly knowledgeable about what he teaches and expects you to thoroughly engage with the content. Hes very understanding too. Most grades are from reading quizzes and a couple papers throughout. Shouldn't take this class unless youre genuinely interested in foreign policy, but if you are and you care youll love it.
You do need to go to lecture and take notes, but the class is very interesting and not too hard. Prof  is nice and pretty personable.

This class was engaging and interesting, and Dr.  is very accessible and passionate about sociology. Her grading is extremely fair, and she created a fun classroom atmosphere and listened to students. She'll push you to expand on your answers, but she's receptive to different perspectives.
Great teacher that really cares about her students.

Mary is the best professor I've had. She is incredibly kind and understanding, so it's okay to miss class- but the material is SUPER important to get. Plan on going every lecture. The readings and topics can be difficult, but she is a phenomenal and engaging lecturer. Always well-prepared. Fascinating class! Fair grading.
just dont take it if you have other hard classes. she deducts points on not having comma on the essay.

One of the most genuine professors I've had at OSU. She really showed that she cared about us and adjusted the syllabus and assignments to make it as easy as possible for us during the pandemic. The assignments and exams are very easy as long as you do the readings and listen to the lectures (she goes over the reading's main points in lecture).
Dr. 's class is so interesting. She is extremely knowledgeable about the topic and amazing at her job. She is funny and so helpful. Highly recommend.

As an online class Professor  was terrible. She just assigned reading in the book, made us take a quiz after every chapter (15) and had 3 exams. She does not give extra credit and did not record lectures.

She is so fun and you can tell she genuinely cares about her class and students. She has tons of experience and stories and is very easygoing. She posts the learning objectives which follow the textbook, so studying for exams is very easy and she definitely isn't trying to trick you in the exams. Highly recommend taking her.

Mary is one of the funniest and most engaging professors Ive had thus far. The class is very lecture-oriented and requires you to read the textbook in order to do well on the exams, but if you study then you should be fine! Shes very passionate and knowledgeable, and its an extremely interesting class to take assuming youre interested in law!

A sweet,Lovely woman, shes really a gem and wants all her students to succeed. Show up to class, all the tests are based on the readings and lecture notes. If you want an A,SHOW UP to class. The material is hard to follow but if you ask for her help she will make sure you have a clear understanding of the material. The tests r all multiple choice

Dr.  is one of the BEST professors and faculty at OSU! He is very professional, caring, and willing to help students pass his course(s). His teaching style and compassion for students makes attending OSU worthwhile. He certainly had a positive impact on my graduate school experience. I highly recommend him! Dr.  rocks!

Dr.  has a ton of cool experience he brings to the course. I think for some the material could be dry, but he made it so interesting. I found his lectures so useful, interesting, clear, and concises that I sent them to my former health research coworkers. This was the most useful course of my MPH so far, & his expertise is critical to that.

Dr.  was great. This class was my second time having him and while he is a little monotoned, his lectures show that he a professional in his field. I learned a lot from him, and I will say that is very receptive to any and all feedback whether it be content from lectures or how the class is structured!
Good guy, wants you to learn in fun ways. Doesnt just push tests or massive papers.

this class was super interesting and I really enjoyed it! Easy A if you do the work!!! I would say I spent an average of 30 min per week on this class and got an A. The actual class sessions are super easy and lowkey.  is very kind and understanding and knowledgeable in his field. Guest lectures are usually very good as well. Class can be long

Dr.  makes this class so much fun! If you don't have an interest in PubH, don't take it. There's a paper every week, 3 short answer questions every other week, and one 3-hour presentation (not as bad as it sounds). If you do the work and put in effort, you'll get the A. But it's a lot of work

's class is kind of a unique animal. He's unbelievably intelligent and a wealth of knowledge (although he does go on a lot of long-winded tangents), and it can be tempting to skip class, but he knows who shows up consistently and who doesn't. If you go to class almost always and act at least somewhat engaged, you'll be successful.
Very boring lectures, doesn't use visual aid, grade comes down to midterm, final, research paper

Lectures not mandatory. If you read the books you don't need to go. Such a nice and brilliant man. Long paper assigned, and is expected to be heavy in statistical data. Even if you go to lecture, buy the book. It's very hard to take notes and stay focused. Great man
is an expert on Congress and highly recommended. Personable, entertaining class, and genuinely cares about his students
Dr. 's course can be challenging, but he is highly supportive of students. Well worth the effort you need to put in. He is an expert on Congress.
Dr. 's course is very challenging, but worthwhile. He is an expert on Congress and is definitely worth the time.
Doctor  is an expert on Legislative Politics. The class is rigorous, but you will learn a great deal.  is an excellent professor and is highly recommended.

Mr.  is a really nice guy. His style is very dry though. I wish he would use more powerpoint or other visuals. He lectures almost the every class of the quarter. Not very exciting. Had to write a long paper and had two exams in the class.
grades very hard, couldn't really help with the essay
Very friendly and very intelligent, but appallingly dry lectures. He reads straight from a prepared script in a monotone voice.
Very intelligent instructor who explains things thoroughly. Only three grades in the glass. Make sure you read the books!

Lectures were a NIGHTMARE. I could not make it through one lecture without leaving. I literally was falling asleep by the break. He is a very nice guy and he knows his stuff, but he is impossible to deal with in a group/lecture setting. The exams were not hard. PS majors should know alot of the info already. paper was uncalled for! 17 pages!

did a very good job teaching the course. He is very smart and this showed in his lectures. Dr.  is very passionate about legislative politics. The class is easy, though there are quite a few books (a fair amount for a 500 level class). Responds to emails very fast and is a nice person.

Very difficult professor. Grades without a curve. Unclear about what is expected, very picky about what you write. Gives out Cs even without explanation about what is wrong with assignment/exam. Avoid!!

Though Prof.  is an amazingly nice man, I'm not sure if I could stand to sit there for 10 weeks again. The tests and essay were easy, but lectures were not at all helpful to the class. Refers you to sections of the book and spends nearly an hour talking about what poli sci majors should already know-- the political news. nice guy but do avoid

The most boring political science class I have ever taken! He basically speed reads from the book, and takes the entire time each session. Will never answer a question straight forward. Gives you a study sheet for the midterm but expects you to remember every little detail. Avoid!!!!!!!
neutral
Exams are slightly hard but not ridiculous. She's a decent professor and topics are actually interesting.

The class was a positive experience, but could get dry sometimes. She read pretty much directly off the slides, but attendance was a must because we would have surprise in-class assignments which counted as an attendance grade. Grading criteria for her assignments could have been a bit clearer, but she was friendly and responsive to emails.

Dr.  is a great professor. As long as you do the reading and attend lectures, the class is very easy. She also curves the exams if many students struggle with certain questions and offers extra credit opportunities. If you do the work, it is very easy to get an A. Also, the lectures are info heavy but still interesting.

the exams are terrible. They donot even seem that hard while you are taking them, but she grades like a hound. Average of the first exam was a 68, no curve. She offers little extra credit and the only plus is she drops the lowest 8 quiz grades, but with the exams being worth 70% of ur grade it does not really matter now does it. I would avoid it.

Toughest political science course I have taken at OSU. The course takes a scientific approach to identity and ethnicity which means you are put through a meat grinder of reading material throughout the semester. You will not pass if you are not keeping up with the readings. Everything is fair game on exams. Write everything down!

Dr.  is a tough prof, but if you do the readings then you can do well. While there are a lot, they're very instructive on nat'lism and ethnicity. She's a brilliant scholar, and if you are thinking about research then she's a great person to ask for help. Grading is mostly exams plus reading quizzes. You get out of the class what you put in.

Dr.  is brilliant, but her class is way harder than it has to be. Super difficult reading quizzes, and lots of stuff on tests that were hardly covered. Interesting class, but I definitely would not take it again.

While  clearly knows her material, she is extremely monotone and doesn't get students engaged or involved. The material can seem a little repetitive and it would have gone smoother if the class structure was different.

Dr.  taught such an amazing class. I learned so much and the assignments were sort of fun. We had a presentation and paper and I actually sort of enjoyed those. The exams also weren't bad, they were online and open note. There are small reading quizzes everyday, but if you read they are super easy. Loved this class.

has a lot of potential to be a good professor. But she is awful. Her class is asinine, the study guides are no help on the tests, and she's boring. Dozens of pages of reading each night. I would not take this class if I were forced to. It's way so hard it's not worth it.
This is the third class I have taken with Dr. . Although you have to work for an A, her classes will teach you a ton and she is extremely intelligent and well respected in her field.

This was the first time Democratic Erosion was offered at OSU and Prof.  did a great job with it even though it's not her area of expertise. Lots of reading (about 100 pages/wk), but workload is manageable all things considered. Hopefully OSU continues to offer this course and has her teach it at least a couple more times!
Seems to really care about how her teaching is going and how she can improve herself. Reading quizzes for each class, but they are only like two easy questions each.

Dr.  is great! She is extremely passionate and knowledgable about the material being covered. She also gave us a one sided sheet of paper as a cheat sheet for the exams. There is paper and presentation that take some effort, but its certainly not absurd amount of work. The hardest part of the course was the map quiz on Africa

She is extremely knowledgable and loves what she teaches. Class can get boring at times and she may not be as engaging but she cares about the subject a lot. She is a VERY VERY TOUGH professor in grading exams and constructing them. Be prepared to work hard. I got an A but considering the amount of coursework, the class should have been a 4000.

is a great teacher. She really wants her students to do well. She makes sure to ask students if her current teaching style is working and reworks the curriculum to help the students learn better. If you pay attention and stay on main points you'll do fine. A good person overall.

One of the best courses I have had here at OSU! Dr.  is an excellent professor and I would take anything that she taught. The lectures were engaging and fun. Not your average poli sci class, she teaches using a variety of disciplines and challenges you to think for yourself. Very helpful in office hours and gives points back on exams.

Good instructor. She's loves what she teaches and has experience. Very nice approachable and friendly. Gives pop quizzes over readings to do random attendances checks. Tests and lectures are straightforward

Fantastic professor. I took the OPEEP Psych 1100 class and although it was somewhat disorganized at times, he always made sure the students were taken care of and made sure that they have the ability to succeed. Very caring professor and a very humble person. Readings were very heavy at times, however they became easier to manage over time

Dr.  is very invested in your success. He could be driving, eating, or sleeping but he will still take the time to answer your question. It is an easy A if you follow his instructions which are clear. The course is also very organized.
Amazing professor!!! all that needs to be said

Dr.  is a solid professor. Can be a bit of a boring lecturer but hes happy to discuss subjects with you and is interested in teaching. Hell tell you you dont need the book to pass but that youll need it if you want an A which is definitely true. Lots of extra credit and he posts all of his lecture notes before class.

I cant begin to explain how much this professor cares about how his students are doing in the class and how much they ENJOY the class. He constantly is looking for feedback on how he can further change the course so that it can help our intro psych experience. There is extra credit literally every week and going to tutoring gets you extra credit!

Dr.  gives out extra credit like candy on Halloween. This semester, he gave out 70 points of extra credit out of 500 total points, so if you get all of the EC and try in the class, you are well underway for an A in the class.

Makes the material enjoyable to learn and easy to understand. Really sweet and caring. Totally accommodating to the students. Posts his lectures on Carmen. Gives a lot of extra credit so if you don't do well it's on you. Professor aside, he's really such a great guy and I'd strongly suggest taking him. Also, don't buy the textbook bc its useless.

Professor  actually genuinely cares about you. He will make time for one-on-one study sessions and offers TONS of extra credit. The material itself is challenging, but with the EC, you'll pass with flying colors. The only downside is that he spends a lot of time pushing his political agenda in class. All things considered, I recommend him.

Tests are straightforward. Lot's of extra credit. Don't really need a textbook and there is no online stuff which is awesome. His study sessions saved my butt and is a really nice guy and is very lenient on grading.
Boring, not necessarily hard. just really boring
Very kind professor that is very passionate about his work. Not only that, but he is very communicative and is always accepting of feedback.

This class takes effort. Attendance is important and its a lot of work. But, Dr.  puts in the effort to make the class interesting. He is passionate about the subject and cares that his students are experiencing this passion too. He encouraged my interests and helped me explore EHS careers. put in the effort and you'll be fine

After experiencing both Covid and depression and receiving a doctors note for both of these issues, Dr. would not unlock the current modules so that I could catch up and stay current in the course. Instead he forced me to continue doing them in order, even though each module is unrelated to the others. Doesn't seem to care about the students.

This was a course more about finding scientific resources and interpreting at scientific information than it was about climate change and human health (the title of the course). It felt fairly disorganized, with difficult to interpret instructions for homework and a heavy load of busy work.

This class is easy and there are no exams or quizzes. You basically work on a semester long project with your group every week. There are homework assignments and journals. The assignments are very easy they both took me no longer than an hour at best. Everyone ends up with an A. I ended with a 99% A.

This class at its roots is easy. There are no exams and your grade is based mainly around a semester-long group video project. The topics are interesting and Dr.  is very passionate about his field. However, the class is not organized well and is heavy in "busy work".

Dr.  is scrambled most of the time and the entire class is busy work and one meaningless group project. It is extremely easy, just follow the rubric and turn in assignments. Each week there is a reflection, homework, learning activity, and group project stuff due. It's not a lot I swear, it's super easy no exams. Turn stuff in and participate

Dr.  is an amazing professor! Her class is discussion and activity based so be sure to make friends in the class. She has clear expectations of her students and really make sure that the material we learn in class can be applied in real world setting!! Overall, definitely recommend!!

I am surprised at all of the not so great reviews here. I absolutely loved Dr. ! Her lectures are very interactive and discussion based, answers all questions. I recommend asking questions and talking because it really helped me to learn the information. Gives a lot of extra credit opportunities and quizzes are simple if you go to class.

Really great class. Discussion based class, with two readings & response papers a week. The readings were always really interesting and the way she led discussion sparked a lot of inspiration. Taking her again next semester and really looking forward to it.

Dr.  is my favorite professor at OSU. Her lectures are much more discussion based, which some people may not like, but I really enjoyed it. Im going to be taking my third class with her next semester. Shes so caring and definitely prioritizes the well-being of her students. I have nothing but good things to say about her class!

She was not helpful at all, and was often rude to students. Lecture was mandatory (unfortunately) but class work was fairly easy. The weekly reading assignments were very annoying at first, but you were luckily able to work ahead in the class. Overall, I dont recommend, I learned basically nothing.

I really enjoyed her class, but I will say that if you're planning on skipping a lot (like me), you will lose quite a few participation points. There were weekly journal articles, but they weren't super hard and didn't take a lot of time. Class discussions were always interesting and she definitely makes it an open space for lots of opinions.

I really liked Professor s class and looked forward to going every week. The material was interesting, and she taught in a way that made lectures enjoyable. This is the second class of hers Ive taken, and I am going to take a third because I think shes one of the best professors Ive had!

I had to end up dropping this class and replaced it with abnormal psych. She does not share PowerPoints, and goes way too fast. Extremely boring and quizzes are very difficult. All the quizzes and exams are online except the final. Textbook does not correlate with lecture. Pop up assignments given at the end of lecture and due before you leave.

I heard such good things about Dr.  but I hated her class. She made it very clear from the beginning of the semester that her convenience is more important than us. She didn't want to make homework more accessible because it would be annoying for her to grade. She has also been extremely rude at times and let full-on fights break out in class.
not too bad. never get behind on the lectures. youll regret it when its exam time guys ..

she was an alright professor but you definitely have to take notes and go through the textbook. you wont pass without at least doing that because her questions u cant look up and are usually directly from the her lectures or textbook. she doesnt give a lot of homework at all but its important to do good on quizzes and tests.

I wasn't a huge fan of Dr. . She tended to go off topic in the beginning of class (the first 15 minutes) and then towards the end of her lecture time, she would rush through the slides because she didn't have enough time. Slides were never posted either. I felt uncomfortable asking her questions bc of how she talked to students.

Dr  makes her classes interesting and entertaining, and I looked forward to it despite it being an 8 am. She has specific criteria for her classes, and expects you to follow them, but truly cares about the students she teaches and is very fun to talk to when you have questions. I loved her personality and her teaching style. Plus no tests!
Slides arent posted online. Exams are applying knowledge Not just memorizing. One project, 3 midterms and 1 cumulative final. Got a better grade because of extra credit so do it!

Lots of presentations and projects, but no exams! She's an amazing lecturer and you can tell she really wants to help us. Attendance is definitely a must though or you won't do well. She's a pretty generous grader and is generally very understanding. Worth noting: she handled the COVID-19 situation amazingly and was very clear & open about changes.

Shes definitely one of the best lecturers Ive ever had. She makes you really want to engage with the material and it is insanely easy to get an A. Youll hate her if youre the type to not show up to class since its mostly designed around participation and in-class work. Ive taken other courses she teaches and I very strong recommend them too.

I did not enjoy Dr. 's teaching style, she had group work for such a large lecture class and wasted a lot of time doing so. Rushed through a lot of slides and didn't post slides online. One midterm and one cumulative final, though they both were only worth 12.5% of the grade. Only reason I got an A was the crazy amount of extra credit she gave.

Dr.  is a great professor! You learn a lot in her class, much more than most of the other classes I've taken in the psychology department. She's understanding and tries to explain things in a way that everyone will get them

Her class is easy, but pretty annoying. She's not very clear on some of the project criteria and not willing to work with you if you miss ONE class. There are pop quizzes over readings and a project. She also doesn't post her lecture slides online, which makes studying for the midterm and final a little intense. its hard to know what to focus on.

Dr.  is awesome! There are no exams in this class, so everything is based off of attendance and projects. They're really straightforward and if you just follow her instructions, you'll be fine. I learned a lot in this class and will retain way more of it than if I had just been memorizing definitions for a Scantron. Take her class!

Incredibly smart and educated professor. Great class. Lots of information in a short amount of time. Very quiet speaker but values opinions and discussion. Not an easy A but you will get a lot out of this class if you put the effort in.

One of the smartest / best professors I have had at OSU. This class will stretch your mind and you will grow as a student. Very discussion based. However, this is not an easy class. Does not round grade. You will have to put in a lot of work. You will be able to use what you learn in her class in other classes. Highly recommended

She is so engaging and wants everyone to do well in class. She is big on participation during discussions but if you talk to her she will include you in the discussions. Easily accessible outside of class. Her class is not an easy A, but probably one of the smartest professors in the Political Science department. Can not recommend her enough!

Dr. is a phenomenal instructor and keeps the class engaged. She provides clear instructions and keeps everything organized. She provides excellent feedback on papers and she gives great advice about research.

Amazing professor, challenging but wildly interesting & enjoyable course. Dr.  was very supportive, always accessible outside of class, seems genuinely invested in students' growth. I never felt overlooked even as an undergrad in a graduate course. One of my favorite classes/profs to date!

This was one of my favorite classes. Professor  is so smart and our readings and lectures were always very engaging and interesting. It was not too hard either as long as you show up, engage and do the readings. I really enjoyed this class and got a lot out of it.

An absolute queen. She is one of my favorite professors at Ohio State. The class can be hard, but it's doable as long as you stay on top of the readings and show up every day. She encourages you to explore your own ideas in papers and she is one of the smartest people I've ever met. Really knows the ins and outs of political theory. Overall 10/10

She is so nice and helpful. If you have any suggestions, she is always willing to listen and is always looking to improve your learning experience. Definitely do the reading though and definitely participate. She was never judgmental of the ideas you have and always willing to explore them in more depth. Overall I really like her as a professor.

Very difficult but rewarding class. Took this for my minor and it was one of my favorites of the semester. I think it's a testament to a professor about how they handled the COVID-19 situation and ESH made the transition smooth and was very understanding. She is obviously very intelligent but is a tough grader, and the class has a LOT of reading.

This course is very objective, it is almost all based on philosophy. If you don't have an original idea or agree with prof. you may receive a bad grade on papers on tests. She grades off how much effort she thinks you gave. Also, she will tear you apart in your papers even though there are no clear-cut guidelines on what she really wants.

Dr.  definitely knows what shes doing; shes clearly knowledgeable on analyzing political arguments. 3440 was extremely reading intensive, but the readings were all valuable and had a clear purpose in the course. Shes super approachable; 10/10 would recommend.

Dr.  is extremely knowledgeable on many topics and conceptualizes political theory like none other. The class however, is extremely reading-intensive, and it can be very easy to fall behind in the difficulty and the amount of readings given. Dont take her class if youre looking for an easy grade-booster, youll get the opposite.

Dr.  is outstanding. Her class is demanding, but it was the most intellectually engaging class I've taken in college. She is wicked smart, accessible outside of class, and is really caring and gives positive feedback. She is overall incredible and so good at guiding class discussion and analyzing the nuances of political theories.

Do not take this class if you want your grade to be determined by 4 things. 2 of the grades in this class are done by the TA and the other 2 are a midterm and a final. There is no and I mean NO wiggle room if you do poorly on one assignment. All the "answers" in this class are subjective which should lean towards leniency but there is none.

I absolutely loved having Prof. ! Shes incredibly intelligent, and she very much knows her way around political theory. Some of the readings were dense, but she was very understanding and approachable about them, and it was quite apparent how thoughtfully she put together the syllabus. I would die for her, honestly. Amazing prof.

Prof  is so smart and knowledgable. I learned sooo much from this class and it was super interesting. It's not the easiest class but if you put in a decent amount of effort there's no reason you shouldn't succeed.

This class was very enjoying and I learned a lot from it. We rarely had homework and honestly, I finished most of the week's work in an hour. Definitely recommend taking ay class you can with this professor.

Do NOT take a class with . When I had a family emergency, she essentially told me that I needed to have done the work on time and turn it in on time. Very few chances to get your grade up if you miss a discussion/reflection. Will be petitioning for grade forgiveness and taking class with any other intro professor. AVOID IF ABLE

is by far the worst professor I have ever had. She is incredibly rude, and does not provide any detailed feedback, no matter if she claims she did. She is a horrible grader, she is extremely strict and only gives you the link to the rubric as "feedback". AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!!!!
She is kinda rude and goes back on her work

She doesnt allow any technology in her class room despite the university providing us with iPads and encouraging us to use them. So I everything for my classes on the iPad except for this class. She docked my grade twice for one paper.

The greatest prof. I have ever had. It is clear what she expects from you so if you do what she says, the classes are pretty easy. If you take notes from her power points, there is no reason you shouldn't do well on the exams. She is younger, so I think that she understands the students more. Always willing to help, or just talk if you want.

She's very specific on what she expects in the papers. If you follow along with the rubrics given, you will do well. Proofread your papers SEVERAL times. The papers are not long, but she doesn't like what she calls "word fat." Exams are written, but she provides a study guide and those were helpful. If you go to class and study, you will do fine.

Not many points available, only 200 for the whole Social Psych class, yet a tough grader and she even said "you won't get 100% on some papers". No extra credit available. I found myself struggling to get every point I could.

I too am an untraditional student, and I really enjoy 's class. You know what to expect and where you stand. Put the required work in and you'll be fine. She challenges you in hopes that you will learn something. She is really nice and offers help if needed through email, office hours or after class.

is great, she spells out the expectations in the beginning, if you aren't up to it, drop. Class and lectures are enjoyable, be prepared to be challenged and actually learn something. Very aproachable, wants your patricipsation and feedback. As untraditional student, I find her class enjoyable! Notes are clear, tells you what to write down.

This prof has unrealistic demands and expectations. I wonder if she realizes we are full time students. She is picky and sensitive about everything. Between quizzes after EVERY chapter and writing 7 papers, and one big paper and the midterms--which you have to take meticulous notes because she makes it clear she won't provide you with any. Run!

Three quizzes, three exams. Final exam is noncumulative. Very direct and to the point. Randomly passes around a sign-in sheet to gauge attendance. NOTE: If you're under 18, you have to write EIGHT summaries of research papers to get research credit (10% of grade). If you're over 18, you get to participate in experiments for that credit instead.

I definitely not recommend taking this class with her. She is super nice, but nice well experienced with the material. She reads from slides most of the time and her exam questions are not related to what she gave in the lecture.

Hard class but makes you think. Expects a high level of understanding of journal articles. Fun lectures and she obviously cares about the material. Presentations have to be well thought out. Be prepared to discuss the articles in class. Debate at the end of the semester helps bring it all together.

Like a lot of grad classes in psych I found this one to not be very informative. I learned a few things. Some of it was repeated from lower level courses, or the lectures were very mundane. Graded items are three presentations, and short weekly response paper to articles, which are difficult to read. Make sure your presentations are very detailed.
You do need to go to lecture and take notes, but the class is very interesting and not too hard. Prof Reczek is nice and pretty personable.

This class was engaging and interesting, and Dr. Reczek is very accessible and passionate about sociology. Her grading is extremely fair, and she created a fun classroom atmosphere and listened to students. She'll push you to expand on your answers, but she's receptive to different perspectives.

Dr.  was an amazing lecturer! There was a situation I had where I had submitted something late, but after explaining my situation, she allowed me to get full credit for it. 2 of the discussion posts and readings are dropped, and there are plenty of opportunities for extra credit. Make sure you don't wait until last minute to do the work!

Dr.  is such a genuine human and professor! Her class is easy and straightforward, consisting of discussion boards and article summaries. I had an issue with COAM for another class as she and my other class had the same prompt of writing my personal immigration history. She was so understanding and even wrote a letter advocating for me.

Dr.  is very passionate and informed about the work she does. Her lectures were interesting but not mandatory you can still get an A without them. The textbook was only for the quizzes and it is free online and there are weekly reading discussions and extra credit opportunities throughout the semester. Would def take her again,

Though this class did have a weekly reading and discussion post due it truly is not that bad. There is a ton of extra credit available and three discussions and a reading summary get dropped. This is an easy A class just don't wait till the last second to do the work.
I really enjoyed taking this class with professor . The workload was manageable and the course was super interesting.
Dr.  is one of my favorite professors at OSU! Definitely take a class with her if you get the chance.

Professor  was an amazing professor for Sociology 3302! This class was offered online over the summer and was seriously the easiest A I have ever received (plus, it's a 3 credit hour course). It is an easy GPA booster if you need an easy class! I recommend taking it online
What a waste of my time. Easy A though.

This is a very writing and reading heavy course. There are required readings weekly and each reading is around 15-25 pages long. Plus textbook reading and smaller readings. If I would have known this was a reading and writing course, I wouldn't have taken the class.

Dr.  was a really engaging professor and had a very well organized course. However, she is very inflexible when it comes to formatting and submitting assignments. The content of her course is not very difficult however she makes things more complicated than they should be.
Dr.  is extremely caring and exceedingly smart. Her class is engaging and expects engagement from students as well. Grading was fair and extra credit was abundant.

Dr.  is inexperienced as a political science teacher, but I'm confident she will continue improving. The class was structured in a way that makes getting an A easy, Dr.  is funny and willing to take feedback.. She gives opportunities for extra credit and she works hard to make sure the class discusses many points that may not be popular

Make sure you do the readings otherwise you wont pass (LOTS of reading). Her midterm and final are both part multiple choice/fill in and part essay turned in on Carmen. Class is very liberal and one-sided on topics. Lots of opportunities for extra credit. I wouldnt recommend unless youre very passionate about immigration topics.

Professor 's online class was one of my easier classes. It was asynchronous and consisted of weekly readings (25-30 pgs.), video lectures with slides (about 1 hr.), an application activity (1 paragraph), and short quizzes that are open note. It may sound bad, but there's a one week grace period and multiple (a lot) extra credit opportunities.

Prof  was a great professor. Lectures averaged about 1 hour long. There was a weekly quiz and discussion. There is a one-week grace period. Overall this was a straightforward class. Some of the TA's grade harshly but not professor .

Took his asynchronous course and it was perfect for my busy schedule. Each weekly module consisted of a 30ish page reading, an hour long pre-recorded lecture, an (easy) quiz, and a 2 paragraph application assignment. Just take notes on the readings and lectures and you will be fine quizzes are open book, too! The man is also very funny.

Overall this class was no too hard. Doing the readings were a must and taking very detailed notes on book and lecture videos. He makes questions a little too specific sometimes but overall and easy class.  was very passionate about this course and gives lots of extra credit.
He is an amazing professor. He gives lots of extra credit. Would recommend.

I took Intro to Sociology online with Dr.  and his class was very well organized. 1 quiz and 1 small writing assignment were due every Sunday. The TAs are more likely to respond faster than the actual professor.

This class was a great course for getting feet wet into classes at OSU. In my personal opinion, this asynchronous course allowed plenty of time to finish coursework throughout the entire semester. Professor  was amazing in how much extra credit that you received during the semester. The textbook is an easy read, the assignments are easy.

There were multiple times I reached out to Prof  and (if) I got a reply, I legit said aloud, "well thanks for nothing." I cannot express how impersonal this class was. I understand it was asynchronous but I literally felt like I was 100% teaching myself. It was so hard to keep up with the lengthy readings and long lectures. Do not recommend.
Pretty chill teacher overall. Watch the lectures and read the textbook and you'll pass just fine.

Honestly a really nice guy. His class was completely asynchronous and every week there is a quiz and application. I did struggle with some quizzes because of the amount of reading and lecture notes to write down but he offers a lot of extra credit opportunities! Overall, good class just watch and study the content. Also give grace periods!

One of my best professors so far! The only reason I got a B in this class was because I had a few missing assignments from being lazy on my part. Two assignments per week, the quizzes are super easy and open book. The essays are fairly easy as well as long as you understand information. Dr.  was super understanding with the pandemic!

Wasnt my favorite class but dr.  was very kind and helpful. I took this class online and there were weekly readings, lecture notes and quizzes. Then there are 2 essays and a final project. Everything was fairly easy and theres a lot of extra credit. If you think you deserved a higher grade on the essay, just ask him to look it over again

Classwork is done on your own time. There was one assignment and quiz a week along with 2 papers for the semester. No midterms. There is a final project but no final. TA is very helpful and responds quickly. Lectures are iffy sometimes but usually helpful. Sometimes the quiz questions were a little specific. If you read, quizzes aren't that hard

Three open note midterms, two papers and one course project, so not a lot of work outside of class, but you have to do well on all the exams/projects. He is accessible outside of class to go over exam questions that were missed. He also gets rid of questions on the exams if a significant amount of people miss the same question. Great guy!

The essays dragged my grade from a A to a B, which was a bit annoying because they were graded by the TAs not him. As a lecturer, I had a hard time keeping focused during class, I feel like he went on a tangents. Otherwise, he's a funny guy. He could stick a mic under your face during class, happened to me once and I just said "I don't know."
Super nice guy, very caring of the class and students and it shows. Attendance isn't mandatory and exams are open book and online. Super easy class.

Dr.  is a wonderful and funny professor and I very much enjoyed his class. The exams are open book, open note, and do not have to be taken in the classroom. He has very few grades, but if you put in the effort, you'll get a good grade. He posts all the notes online and reading the book isn't necessary, but helpful. Positive and happy guy.

Dr.  is awesome! You can tell he cares about his students and sociology. His exams are all open note, open textbook, open google... and he ends up taking questions off that were commonly missed. The two 3 page essays given throughout the semester are the only work that you will have to do for this class, but youll still end up learning a lot

he is a great professor but the exam is really hard although it is an open book exam. The paper instruction is not clear at all so a lot of people ask questions in-office hours. Prepared to wait for at least 30 min for the office hour.

Tbh I literally didn't go to class, went the first week then never showed up again. He posts all his slides and the exams are online so basically I just had those up while I took exams, ended the semester with an A- so I wouldn't say you have to go to class. Also never used the textbook so I wouldn't recommend buying it.

Wish more of my online classes were like hers. Simple, straightforward format with lectures that were just the right length, and plenty of opportunities to practice for exams and ask questions. Also loved the fact that she talked about students' research interests during office hours! She' great at communicating and responds to emails quickly, too.
She's amazing! Make sure you take one of her classes before you graduate!!!
She is so sweet and caring! Her material is super straightforward so exams are too.

Dr. Sullivan is a great professor. She is super knowledgeable and her exams are very straightforward. If you attend lecture and take good notes, you should be fine! Make sure to read/watch the supplemental materials also!

she's so nice and funny and keeps lectures really entertaining and clearly knows what she is talking about. she has made me consider getting a career in something with the psychology of children and or family psychology she is super sweet and understanding as well. if you watch the lectures and do the reading the exams aren't bad at all.

Dr. Sullivan is a gem. She clearly is passionate about the subject matter, and her heart for the students and content is evident. She is passionate and intelligent, and I learned so much without really trying.

Dr. Sullivan gives INCREDIBLE lectures. Her lecture slides are pretty simple, so going to class and listening to what she elaborates on is really important. Her tests are easy and straightforward. She's also an angel and wears the best outfits.

His lectures are okay. There can be really interesting content, but sometimes he just goes on unrelated rants. He says he's a realist every time he gets a chance and says some really out of pocket stuff sometimes but in a funny way. Class is super easy though, I would take it if you need a GPA boost.

Apparently  is famous in the IR field and a fine teacher who explains different IR theories well. Easy class - never showed up in person, watched a few recordings, grinded on the paper before ddl, and got 100% on both midterm and final.
Never showed up and got an A. Didn't learn anything.

Dr  is one of the most interesting teachers I have had at OSU. All of his lectures are interesting, and they are extremely helpful to expanding the way you think critically about international politics. Even his inane ramblings are interesting. The readings are very well chosen. Cannot recommend this Professor enough

Professor  had some interesting lectures, but would also go on random rants about weird stuff (he's very pro-Trump, and has a tendency to talk over people even if they agree with him). The course itself is not hard at all - a couple of big exams that are very hard to do badly on.

Class is graded by two tests and nothing else. He posts all of the lecture notes and powerpoints online. Also posts the midterm and final so you know exactly what will be on them. Will constantly tell you he's a realist. Amazing course to take during the pandemic. You won't regret it.

Professor  is super opinionated. His lectures are extremely boring but not necessary as long as you understand the general concepts/theories from the powerpoints. The only grades are a midterm and final, and both are essays (he's not a hard grader). Overall, an easy class, but my least favorite professor ever.

Professor  is awesome! He doesn't want to tank your GPA or make your life difficult for no reason. The entire class is graded by your midterm and final. He gives you plenty of resources on Carmen (including past tests ;) ) I 100% recommend taking this class.

Prof. s class was very, very easy. Our final exam was completely opinion-based, and we didnt have to cite any of the class material for the essay. He doesnt care about killing your GPA and making your life miserable for a semester he really just wants you to learn, and thats your choice if you do or not. Hes a nice guy!

Professor  is an amazing professor! Hes really laid back and doesnt try to make your life miserable! Hes very precise with the exam questions and if you pay attention in class youll pull through with an A. Class is all exams and little to no extra credit.

The only way to not get an A is if you literally don't try *at all*. Exam questions are given beforehand. However because of this the class was honestly kind of boring and not worth going to. He's nice but doesn't really care about undergrads but that's not all that unfamiliar in the poli sci department.

This class is dumb easy. Only grades are the midterm and final, but he gives you the questions beforehand and only makes you write a response for 1 or 2 of them. He also gives you the answers to all the questions the lecture before both exams. Dr  is very knowledgeable and decently funny, so lectures arent bad either

Incredibly easy A, but it's a bit boring because of that. Reading isn't required, there's no homework, and there is one midterm and one final, which he grades pretty easily. If you're looking for an easy A this is the class, but if you want something more intellectually stimulating I would find another class.

Wonderful professor, very caring towards students, and offered to meet students over coffee rather than sit in an office. Wants to see everyone do well, and get an A. Will only be graded for midterm and final, but as long as you attend class, read your notes routinely, and ask questions, you will get an A.

Really easy A. Literally show up to class and study a bit for the two exams and you'll get an A. That being sad, he's a really intelligent man with unique ideas, and he loves hearing from his students. If you go to class, you'll learn quite a bit.

A midterm and a final, each worth 50% of your grade. Gives you the essay questions ahead of time, so if you prepare even a little bit for the exams you'll definitely pass if not get an A. In my class over 70% got As on the midterm.

Class lectures can be very dry if you're not into Polisci. He is very laid back and it shows in the class. There are only two grades in the class. A midterm and final. Both are essays that he gives you ahead of time and grades them with a ton of leniency. He is a realist and not afraid to share his opinion
interesting, relatively easy class
He's a good, easy going professor but in case you couldn't tell he reminds you daily that he is a realist

Dr.  is a great professor. This class isn't hard because he makes it clear that he's not trying to make your life hard for no reason. He wants people to get A's and learn. Class always gets out early and he is always available to talk.
Very nice, however her lectures are all discussion and can be boring. The exams are pretty easy (she tells you exactly what will be on them), and the class isn't very hard.

is a bit of a mixed bag. On one hand, she's not that great a lecturer and over assigns readings. On the other, she has an encyclopaedic knowledge of East European politics. Both classes I've been in, she shows a movie. Clearly defined workload (two essay exams, 10-15 pages of writing). Only take if the subject matter interests you.
Rambles during lecture, doesn't facilitate effective in-class discussions, no real course structure.

VERY Difficult and unpleasant person to deal with; does not answer emails on a regular basis; I received an A and did not find the class to be terribly difficult grade-wise; although there was a lot of reading, none of it was very difficult- mostly one-liner articles.

Very advisable to skip reading if you want a decent grade, but not if you want to understand the material. Will not give out A's, but will arbitrarily hand out A-'s. Don't know of anyone who did worse than a B, so, if you're comfortable with a glass ceiling on A's, a good class. EXTREMELY tiring though, not sure if it was her fault or the subj.

Don't waste your time reading the huge course packet she makes you buy. She picks terrible readings and doesn't hold you acocuntable for knowing the content. The class is ok...but she's just not a very likable lady.

I pity anyone who has to take a(nother) class with this woman- she's the worst; I don't mind a hard challenging professor, but she's terribly unpleasant to deal with; she always has a nasty attitude and is off-putting in the extreme; talks down to students.

Her lectures are generally disorganized and boring. I wouldn't recommend saying much-she usually misunderstands what students say. However, she is a knowledgeable instructor and a fair grader. Here's a tip: if she starts shouting, she's saying something she wants you to write down.
Terrible class. Incredibly boring and she expects you to know a ton about international politics coming in. Avoid this class with her at all costs.
No Comments

There was this one class of hers I found really interesting but it must have been a fluke. To sum it up: assumes a lot of prior knowledge, you'll get really good at pretending to be awake, gives all essay tests, assigns readings you shouldn't do, and assigns a lot of papers. I got a B+!

The class was eye-crossingly dull but easy. She isn't very inspiring or entertaining. She has a boring NPR-esque tone that puts you to sleep. She talks in long incoherant sentences much like John Kerry. Reader Beware!
She knows her stuff. Class is challenging, interesting.
GET AWAY
Avoid.
THinks post communism should be our lives 24/7 unrealistic expectations and little clarity......the worst poli sci prof I have had
No Comments
Very mean. Likes to hear herself talk a lot. Don't publically disagree w/ her.
No Comments
Knows subject matter. Likes discussions.

Lectures were very long, often 40 mins to an hour (which was hard to sit through considering it was an online class and there were no closed caption available). His homework assignments were weighed a lot so if you missed one your grade would tank. However exams weren't too difficult, a lot of memorization but that was it.

I found his dry sense of humor to be great. Overall the class was pretty easy to get into and the assignments given were always straight to the point. He can be a bit tough to contact outside of class though, time between emails can be quite a while.
A good professor who enjoys what he does. Sometimes dull but some subject matters are just dull.

He genuinely seems to care about teaching and was always amicable. While his course was a lot to handle due to the amount of material and lectures, he was very organized and responded to emails the day of. Putting in the time and effort to study pays off. Earning an A is 100% possible as long as you stay on track and ask questions as they arise.

Ive taken two of his classes so far, intro psych and stats. His stats was very very time consuming and extremely lecture and homework heavy. However, I still managed to finish with an A as hes super helpful and very clear in what he expects. He tends to take a while to answer emails but tends to be lenient and usually curves tests.

The class was neutral. The only "textbook" used included online articles. He has VERY long lectures that you MUST listen to completely. I also recommend taking notes while watching as well (helps for exams). As for writing assignments, there were only about 4-5 and were required to be about a page long. The only assignments were quizzes and exams!

Lectures are really interesting and usually funny/entertaining. He gives out a paper at the beginning of every unit with exact specifics of what you'll be tested on. Attendance is barely a requirement as he posts all his lectures online at the beginning of the semester.

A great professor. Gives numerous chances for extra credit, take advantage of them. Will finish with a low A. Tests are multiple choice, very few homework assignments that take 5 minutes max. If you halfway study for exams youll be fine.
Take advantage of all extra credit opportunities and study for the exams. He gives you the power point slides, but be sure to take extra notes on them.
Funny guy, realistic, took a lot away from this class. Make sure to pay attention and go to class every time or you will sink.
I enjoyed taking his class. You should go to class and study for exams. Take advantage of extra credit. Overall pretty easy class

Was a very easy going professor, lectures were never boring. You rarely have out of class assignments, but if you do they are very quick and easy. I would definitely recommend, Dr.  is very humorous and very understanding.

This class isn't difficult If you have a strong foundation in math if you don't I would recommend rectifying those problems before taking this class. Study and you will do well. He is very understanding.

Had him for my psych 1100 and my data analysis course. He's a very reasonable professor. And to all the people that said his tests are extremely hard, it's just because you didn't study. Every class I've had with him had two groups, the ones who studied and averaged an A on tests, and those who didn't and blamed him for their failures.
Tests are confusing but was an interesting class and he is a nice guy.

was my favorite professor this semester. His lectures aren't boring, he offers a good amount of extra credit, and the tests are not difficult if you look at the notes. He always tells you exactly what you need to know. If you didn't do well, that was solely your fault for not studying. Textbook is not necessary.

Attendance is not required, but I recommend going to every class. There is a lot of important material that are in the lectures and not in the notes available online. Test are hard, but are curved. Recommend spending a few days studying. HW ends up being worth more than the tests so if you're not a test taker HW can make up for it.
Doesn't respond to emails. Exams are hard and take all day to complete.

Ignores emails asking for help. Homework load is excessive to the point my other classes were affected. Others including myself have had to skip classes in other subjects in order to finish his homeworks on time. He is not flexible whatsoever. Exams are on Friday 6amto9pm, you have to work or go to school? Tough luck!

I enjoyed his class. He doesn't take attendance. He has a sense of humor. If you read your power point notes everyday from class or online you will do good on exam. Quizes are online and would recommend using notes and all time allowed. He curves test and your final grade.

This class was pretty easy- minimal effort put in and got an A. However, this professor is terrible. Her lectures are a joke and her assignments are stupid. Her grading is so odd- it almost seems like she takes off points sometimes to just make it look like she actually reads and grades them. If you want to learn, don't take this class.
I took psych 3325 and she was amazing. Group assignment and homework/quizzes.
one of the smartest and best professors at OSU!!!!

Class was required for my major but very interesting and easy to stay engaged, gave lots of real world examples to make topics clear, if you ever have a question, email her and she'll respond right away

She's a very nice person and a pretty good lecturer that tries to make pretty boring material interesting, but her exams were overly hard. Even though I had pretty much every term from her slides memorized, I still struggled on some of her exams because she asked very nit-picky questions that forced you to know many intricate details.

Dr.  is by far my favorite professor that I have had. She is extremely funny, smart and honestly cares about the students and will go out of her way to help. When it comes to her lectures she is extremely enthusiastic, and can really relate the content to your life and the real world. I recommend signing up for one of her courses.

She really cares that her students do well in the class and gives many opportunities to bring up your grade. Participation matters but she gives more than enough opportunities to earn all the points. She usually tries to end class early, and reviews after every section. She drops 6/11 quizzes and 2/3 written assignments. I would take it again

Overall, a good professor and an easy class. Class was mandatory for my major, but Professor  made the lectures enjoyable. The quizzes were sort of tricky, but easy tests and easily graded paper. did not keep up with any of our work yet he expected a lot out of his students.
