A lot of outside reading. Class could have been A LOT more interesting/enjoyable
Somehow made a very interesting subject boring. Disappointed in this class and wish I hadn't taken it. Did not learn much besides what is covered in an intro psych course.

331 is not that hard. A lot of people are complaining, but I don't know why. I never read the book; I just went to class and studied the notes and got A's on both midterms and final. He curves A LOT, and is very generous w/ grading in my opinion. He is really helpful- offers several review sessions. Take his class; it's not that bad

I was very interested in abnormal psych BEFORE this class. He is extremely biased and is not helpful in explaining the material needed for the exams. Final exam was comprehensive, which, with so much info in the class was nearly impossible. The T.A. never came to class just graded our essays as hard as she possibly could. He ruined it for me.

The class was awesome. It got a little long winded being a 1:48 lecture 2x a week, but he let us take breaks to keep us from getting too restless. He makes the content clear and answers all questions pretty quickly.

The class was very interesting, but was taught in a biased way. It was obvious wich methods and subjects he ageed with or liked the best. Tended to focus on info that wasn't on the test. The TA was useless and didn't attend the lectures but graded the tests which were mostly essay on subject matter covered in class and not in the text.

Dr.  is super laid back. You have a ton of time to finish each module and can honestly get it all done on the due date if you really want to. The course content is interesting and definitely important, and the discussion posts on the content are interesting. If you have a pulse and at least two brain cells, you will get an A in this class.
This class was super interesting and Prof  set it up really well. It was easy to understand and I learned a lot. Definitely recommend!

Dr.  is amazing and it is very evident that he cares! Take PUBHEHS 5320 online with him!! His class is an easy A if you do your assignments. There are 4 modules and you just have to turn in all the assignments by the module due date so you can pace on your own. Dr.  also gives a lot of extra credit! I have over a 100% in his class!

Great, easy class for undergrads. Lots of notes and quizzes, but easy. Keep in mind old quiz questions when taking final exam. Discussion boards, movie tests, and final paper very graded on participation. No textbook. Worst part was he turned off the final grade on carmen so you don't know your grade or "what-if"

Pros:Is an engaging lecturer and assignments are reasonable. 
 Cons:Believes she is more accommodating than she is. Students are able to turn in homework or quizzes three days late twice, not the worst extension policy, but she frames it as being so understanding even though three days is not a lot of time when you're really going through it.

I would recommend taking Dr.  for an upper level neuro class! She is really fun and assignments are pretty easy. Three group projects throughout the semester, but all very manageable. She's very accessible outside of class and fair grader with clear expectations.

She is so awesome she made me switch to neuro, she is hilarious so passionate about her subject and a r engaging and sympthetic professor. I would normally hate a professor if I didn't get an A but I just cant hate her she is an awesome lecturer and makes the material funny and engaging. I'd recommend her to anyone!

Extremely well set up online course. Sends out weekly reminders and wants students to do well. Wants to get to know you when you drop by office hours. If you watch all the lectures, it is pretty easy to get an A. Be prepared to spend about 10-20 hours watching lectures per week, though.

Great prof, she's an excellent teacher. Great at breaking down complex topics and approaching potentially sensitive topics thoughtfully and respectfully. This class was group-project heavy, but it's full of overachieving neuro majors, so you should be fine. There is an emphasis on the real-world application of knowledge and science communication.
I would recommend taking this class because its really hard. The teacher is nice but you will most likely struggle.
Amazingly knowledgeable and informative. Notoriously difficult core class, wasnt so hard online and asynchronous but not sure if it asynchronous still

I had Dr.  for both PSYCH3313 and again for PSYCH4501, and she is just as wonderful. This class is themed around sleep and the brain, and there are no exams -- just three group projects and weekly Carmen quizzes. She cares a lot about the wellbeing of her students and is one of the most understanding professors I've had at OSU.

Dr.  is a very kind lecturer, and I enjoyed Behavioral Neuro! The notes are extremely long, however, and tests are difficult with little time to complete. If you are struggling, Dr.  is a great person to access and is understanding. The coursework is very time consuming, but if youre interested in the topics then its really not horrible.

Phenomenal professor. She really understands her students. Class was very organized and consisted of two assignments, a quiz and a video essay each week. The quizzes come straight from the PPT, the video essays are very simple and are only like a minute long. The assignments can be reading research papers to doing infographics. Cool class too!

Her class was the most challenging one I've taken as a psych major, but it got better later in the semester. Most of the content was learned from the lectures, which could get lengthy. Textbook was optional. Homework/discussions were pretty easy. Biweekly quizzes were worth many points and could be stressful because of time constraints.
The lectures were A LOT, especially for online class, but if you kept up and took good notes her exams were a breeze. Open note, open book (although I don't use the book) and no surprises at all.

Class was completely online and done on your own time. There is a quiz every other week that's worth a decent amount, however, there is a decent amount of extra credit that really helps your grade if you do it. If you have questions office hours can be very helpful. They told many stories told and videos can get tedious but overall decent class

Took this class during the times of Covid so it was all online with pre recorded lectures. I found it very difficult to pay attention during these lectures especially when each module had at least 10 lecture videos. Professor  seems like a great professor, but I wish she would have cut students a little slack during these hard times.

COVID-19: Class was asynchronous, gave lots of opportunities for points via quizzes, assignments, discussion boards. Great lecturer, enthusiastic delivery of material. Assignments could be busy work and somewhat insulting to collegiate level students (scavenger hunt activities?), but fine for the points. Be prepared to keep up with lectures.

So funny and lively! A bright and warm person who keeps students engaged and feeling cared about. Always looked forward to the energy and chuckles. Her exam questions are typically "what does this do, what is its structure, what is its function" or "what would happen if this structure/system was impaired". Know all that and you'll ace :)

Professor  was an awesome professor. I had her in Summer 2020, so things were a bit odd with the new online schooling but she made everything you need easily accessible. It's important to take notes during lectures and can take a bit of time if you take a lot of notes. The lectures and notes you take are important to study for exams.

I have to say, I was nervous to take this course online and dreaded it being one of the harder core topics in Psychology. However, Dr.  makes it really informational and fun to learn. You can tell she loves teaching the topic and has a big interest in aspects of the brain. Would recommend 100 percent. Pay attention to lectures and do the work!

i LOVE dr. !!! shes so energetic & truly makes difficult topics easy to remember through tips, tricks, acronyms, and real-world scenarios. her tests are easy as long as youre attentive and attend her lectures. cant get an A if you rely on just her notes. however, she gives hints on what to study & is always open to questions after class

cares very much for her students and is passionate about the material she teaches. She is on top of emails and willing to meet with students however she can. Three exams and a research project are the major grades. The project isn't bad, but the exams can be difficult if you don't study. Attendance is not mandatory, but I would recommend it.

The classwork was alright but I will never take this professor again due to his stringent grading tendencies. I am a Dean's List student but this is the only class that I have struggled to obtain a B in. This class is not worth the stress and I would recommend selecting an alternative class or professor due to his heavy courseload and expectations

Only 2 papers in the class and a final exam, however there are a lot of readings that are referred to in class and in the final. Lecture tends to be lengthy but interesting and entertaining at times. Prof.  is quite knowledgeable in his field and can convey concepts in an understandable way.

1 Paper, 2 Exams. Each exam had so much content. The exams overall are easy if you can remember 8-9 weeks of content. The lectures are around 50 slides each so each exams has an enormous amount of slides. The class is quite repetitive and you can get lost in the amount of information. Lectures are dry. Paper exams. Only around 2 questions of EC.

taught one class out of 16 weeks. He said the midterm and final "wouldn't be specific," but the tests questions were exactly that. There were over 2,000 total lecture slides between the exams. He makes sure the guest lectures talk as long as possible. Pointless class. Tough grader. Would NEVER recommend this class or professor to anyone.

I read the assignments, attended all but two classes (illness)and took good notes in class. Usually that means an A. Prof. Tasse' taught one class in 14 weeks. Was not even there for the final. Gave only one test--the final on the last day of class with irrelevant questions. I give him an F as a professor.
No Comments

He travelled to Sweden or Germany or somewhere practically every week. Always had someone guest lecture and tests did not come from anywhere! would not recommend this, though he is an interesting speaker.

The material is interesting. However, he did not test over what he taught in class. He also did not test over the book. He admitted at the end of the quarter that he didn't even write his own tests. The grades were so bad he wouldn't even post the averages.

Even though the class isn't assignment-heavy, the tests are pretty brutal. The exams are taken online. I wish we had more time to get them done. This isn't an easy A, btw. If you're looking for that, don't take the class.

Great guy, very knowledgeable & approachable. Lectures r interesting. Provides lecture outlines, but exams will be hard if u don't go to class & take notes. Grade is determined by 3 exams & 1 paper. Paper is easy. Content on exams is easy, MC and ID terms/SA, but very time constrained. Do the readings bc u need to cite them on the exam. Fair class
Dr. is humble instructor and an approachable instructor. He explains everything clearly and makes class entertaining. He is happy to answer questions and give clear feedback.

Professor  knows a lot about what he teaches and is genuinely interested in it, which makes him an excellent teacher. Talk with him when you get the chance, he's friendly and can be very helpful. Show up and take good notes on the slides and you'll do fine.

Dr.  was an excellent instructor. The material was interesting, and he let us apply it to real life. The work was reasonable but make sure that you do well on his midterm and final exams as there are not too many grades in the course. The professor is also very friendly and approachable, so don't be scared to contact or visit him during off

3 exams and a paper, each worth 25%. You have to know your stuff for the exams because he only gives you 50min for 30 multiple choice and 2 short answer questions . You can tell he really enjoys teaching. This makes his lectures entertaining. However, he was prone to getting off topic by answering questions. Lastly, the readings were long and dull.

I recommend this teacher for everyone to take. He is very nice and is easy to talk to. However, you're not graded on too many things so you have to do well on the exams, but overall not that hard of a class to pass and get a good grade in.

Professor  was great this semester. His lectures are PowerPoint led and he explains the main points in the lecture. Study powerpoints for tests and youll pass easily.. attendance isnt mandatory but he does discuss some things on test in class

Super funny and knowledgable guy. Took him for UN Systems 4331 and Environmental Politics 4335 and they were both very informative. You have to attend to understand them though!

Three exams and a paper. No final, and the exams aren't cumulative. Also if you do well on half the exams and the paper, he will probably curve your grade. Mine was curved from a B+ to an A-. Also offers extra credit on your final grade.

Prof.  is great, funny & approacable. There are 3 noncumulative exams and a paper. Exams are MC & then 3 ID terms you write about in detail. Readings show up on the exam but you only need to know the main arguments made in each! DO take if you have an IR focus. Only wish there were study guides for the exams. Other than that I learned alot!

He is very laid back and does not make the class a heavy burden. If you go to class you should do well. Class can get boring often, which is why people skip. Textbook readings are unnecessary but outside readings appear on tests. Three exams (non-cumulative) and a paper. Exams are MC and short answer and mostly straightforward right off his slides

Requires decent effort to do well in the class. Weekly quizzes, 1 midterm, 1 non-cumulative final, 1 term paper, extra credit on research survey & weekly discussion. The class was fairly easy, though I already had some background knowledge. He posts his lectures from the previous year online so you can skip class and not miss much. Only worth going to class for current events, which do show up on exams. 3 exams and a paper, but no study guides for the exams. Questions can be kind of specific.

Very knowledgable professor, he knows the content well. No way to do well in the class without doing the reading and the lecture. The quizzes can be tough, and the Exams are not easy either. Quizzes are difficult, require you to watch the lectures AND do the reading. Lectures are incredibly dry. worse professor ever. never answered my emails when i had questions and put everything off to the TA. everything is timed and now very much time to do it either.

One word: awesome. Prof.  is absolutely hilarious and always presents his lectures very clearly. Overall, a cool guy with info-packed contents.
Hard to focus because he was so attractive. Don't have to do the readings, but look at the abstracts of each one the night before the exam.
Class was useful to attend but not necessary There are a few papers here and there, but mostly the exams are what matters and those are clear cut (exactly what he says in class/ whats on the slides)
he is very considerate for students. I would definitely take his class again

The greatest Math professors in Math department. He explains math concepts clearly and did many examples in class which helps a lot. Exams are fair and he graded it fairly. Just do the homework you will do well in this class.

100% the best professor I've ever had in the Math Dept at OSU. Genuinely cares about his students, even past their understanding of the material. Always happy to meet outside class/office hours if you ask, always answers questions during lecture, and cares about the students learning and enjoying the class. No harsh grading either. 12/10.
Professor  makes the content of the course much more easier than I expected. His lectures are inspirational and informative, and he is also a very approachable person.
The best professor I've ever had. Informative lectures, quick responses, and clear explanations. Take him if you want to pass the course and truly learn something.

Dr.  is who you want for this class. Easily one of the best professors I've ever had. He could not have explained the content of this course in a more clear, easy-to-understand way. Very friendly and caring person as well. Overall, 10/10 professor

Prof.  is a gem, probably the best math teacher I've had. He's down-to-Earth and really cares about you understanding the material. Everything he says makes sense and if you still don't get it, he's pretty accessible outside of class. Highly recommend him!
Amazing professor. Would definitely recommend. Take him!!!!

Informative lectures that help clarify material from the textbook. Cares about students a lot and is helpful in office hours. I disliked the class itself but the professor was so good that he made it bearable.

Joe made a relatively difficult subject very easy to understand. This was my first exposure to mathematical proofs and I'm very glad I had Joe as a lecturer. The exams were very fair and he's a caring person in general so I would definitely recommend.

Professor  is a great math teacher. This class is all proofs and could be very challenging with the wrong professor. Book for the class is helpful and only $10

Dr.  is a caring and passionate teacher and makes sure his students stay engaged and succeed. You really don't need to go to lecture because he just derives equations and it makes everything seem so confusing. If you just do the homework and make sure you understand it all you are truly guaranteed an A on the exams.
WAY TOO MUCH THEORY!! He never did examples which were helpful. Could have skipped lecture every day and just read the textbook.

Joe is a decent professor. His lectures aren't super helpful because he goes into too much theory. However, he does try to "dumb down" differential equations for the class, which helps a lot. Joe  is by far the best math teacher I have had. His explanations to differential equations start basic, and he gradually increases the complexity. The class is comprised of 3 exams, REP assignment and a term paper. Exams are graded very strictly. Professor  made it clear that he was planning to drop my lowest exam, as many on here had said he has done. This did not happen, and after asking to see the breakdown of the grades and get some kind of explanation, I was denied. Disappointed.

Dr.  was a pretty chill professor. Tip: start working on the study guides as you go through the chapters instead of cramming it in before the exam.

Proff  is best described as a "total bro". He explains everything so clearly and has met and worked with half the people they teach about in the book. Very understanding. I bombed one exam and did amazing on the other two so he just dropped the bad one because I asked him nicely and participated in class. I would absolutely recommend.

Prof  was one of the nicest professors I've had. Really into psych and makes the class easy to understand. As long as you do the study guides, you're bound to ace the class. After unfortunately mixing up exam dates, I recieved a very low grade for one of the exams. I explained the sitaution and he dropped the exam from my overall grade. Amazing

SHE IS AMAZING! The material is kinda hard but she makes it so you LEARN it! The exams are reasonable, she gives study guides, extra credit, answers all questions, always replies, and honestly has so much passion for teaching the material! She has a lot of compassion&is friendly. You would be a fool to NOT take this class! It's fun!

I loved Dr.  lecture videos! Her fully online course was so easy to follow. The weekly modules are very manageable. She really cares about her students and knows what shes talking about! I loved how she got students involved with the weekly readings. Make sure you study for her exams and stay on track with the final project early on!
One of the best professors I have had. Very understanding and explains material very well.

You have to keep up with either going to class or reading all the slides (which arent all the way filled out and you learn some terms in class only). It wasn't hard, per se. The lectures aren't all that exciting besides the biweekly activity. She is a good instructor, you just have to pay very close attention

She is the reason why I am minoring in developmental psychology. Her classes were always interesting even though we took a lot of notes!  also made it to were there was no way you didn't understand what she was talking about.
I love her!! She is the best prof. ever!!! I wish I could take all of her classes! I love the way she explains and talks in her lectures! Even just the class topics are very interesting.
a king

Great class to take. Very engaging in lectures. Papers are not too difficult as long as you follow his instructions. Tests are very easy if you read the required material and actually engage in lecture.

Piers is great at making Philosophy interesting and engaging, and often crafts his lectures around group conversation and participation. The only downside is that it can feel disorganized and like its on you to figure out what to study, rather than any clear criteria. If you show up to class and read the material, you should be just fine!

Very solid professor. Super nice and funny little jokes here and there to keep the class awake. Study a couple days in advance for exams and youll be fine.

Intro to ERP was a difficult class only because the concepts were very in depth, but he and the TA went easy on the grading because of this. I really felt like a lot of information was cut out because it was so detailed. This probably could be two or three classes. You will also learn how to code.

Dr. 's class exams were RIDICULOUSLY difficult. He expected you to recall examples from class from MONTHS prior to the exam without informing you that it would be on the exam. He is pretty good. I'd recommend him. My only complaint is he wears sweaters a bit too often for my taste. I think it's unhealthy.

Can be confusing because he doesnt always have text explaining some slides but if you go to class you usually get what he means. Likes to focus on studies behind concepts which is nice. Has some relatively easy hw assignments to help your grade and his exams arent too bad. study 1-2 days for them. Super helpful with questions. Nice guy.

lectures are lengthy and sometimes cause info overload. he really is passionate about cognitive neuroscience but his lectures are tiring. simple assignments and few and far between but article readings are long. be prepared for awkward silences to ensue during lectures.

Sometimes is a bit unclear or a bit dry in lectures, but all in all, he is a really smart dude and really enthusiastic about cognitive neuroscience. The class wasn't very hard to begin with, but he was always very willing to help students and to ensure that everyone succeeded.

A very kind professor. Lectures were interesting, as she didn't read off slides word for word and added insight from what she has learned, or personal experiences. A textbook was not necessary, but an option was given if you needed extra help. Would definitely take her classes again.
great ï¿½ï¿½

Hands down THE best professor here at OSU Marion. Her class was the highlight of my semester, and as long as you do your work and study, you'll do amazing in this class. I have never met such a well-respected, kind, and charismatic professor before! I truly wish her all the best. Thank you for everything, Dr. !
Dr.  is an amazing professor. She definitely cares about your performance in class and will do almost anything to help you be better and understand more. I would 100% take her class again!

Show up and listen to what she says and you pass. Her review sheets are spot on with her exams. If you can answer the questions on the review sheets your golden, also her exams are very simple and easy to understand all you have to do is just study.

Loved Dr. , she makes you work for your grade but provides plenty of feedback and help if you need it. Her lectures were intresting, she gives you full notes and has you fill in the blanks. She's a very nice person, I like her area of study. Enjoyed her class a lot!

Dr.  is absolutely one of the best professors I've ever had. Her expectations are clear, she's more than happy to help, and her experience in the field really shines through. She's a very sweet lady, too! I strongly recommend using the study guides that she provides.

Dr.  is extremely nice and down to Earth. Her lectures are interesting, and she provides powerpoint notes for you to print and bring to class with you. Dr.  is a very nice and laid back teacher. She explains things clearly and provides her power points online to take notes. Not too much from the textbook. She provides study guides for her tests so you know exactly what to expect on her tests. I recommend taking a class with Dr. .

I loved this class. I've taken a few classes with Dr.  and I've enjoyed them all. She doesn't require that you come to class, but if you don't you will miss a lot, especially because we did not use a textbook. You can get an A in the class if you come to class, take the notes, and read over them.
Really good instructor, super interesting and very clear in expectations!
Very nice, clear lectures, extremely helpful and took time to help anyone who needed it. By far one of my best teachers.
Excellent professor! Very organized and equally kind.
She was a great teacher!
She is seriously an awesome teacher
good prof
I have taken one class with her psych 100 and I will not hesitate to take another with her, she is one of the best teachers I have had.
GREAT prof!!! She is so interesting and helpful. The exams are easy if you study and she gives you review sheets as well as optional review class time. I loved her!

A really awesome instructor!!! I am a junior majoring in Psych and will take every class I can with . She makes class fun and genuinely cares about her students.She adds a little personality to her lectures with excerpts from her life. I LOVE her dearly! A+++++ professor!

Dr. DEFINITELY knows her stuff! Have taken more than one class with her and she is just totally awesome! She repeats herself 3 times during note taking so there is no way you can't keep up. EASY notes and interesting, fun lectures. She is EXTREMELY willing to help you succeed in her classes!

She often didn't understand her own material. Unfortunately, she is currently the only professor for PSYCH 3321, which is a required course for B.S. students. My best advice would be to go to the TA's for help, as they probably have a better understanding.

Nothing against  personally, she just doesn't have that firm of a grasp on how students can retain this information. Honestly avoid if you can. Idk how she is with her other courses but she can't teach stats. 3321 doesn't need to be as difficult as she is making it. Doesn't post notes or communicate with TA. Had terms incorrectly defined on her Carmen which is gr8, students learning false info is the goal right? And shes the only one teaching it SP19! Yay OSU:)))

She is so unorganized. Doesnt post the full notes &refuses to answer questions about the HW because shes not the one grading it. The content you think you will be tested on from the HW, notes actice isnt even hard but she asks questions we have never discussed

She skips through the notes super fast, & doesn't post the complete notes online so there's a good chance of missing things. Her exams don't test what we learn. She explains things in the most complicated ways and Ive learned more from teaching myself. Her exams are not like anything done in class, on the homework, or on the exam review problems. Professor is very unreasonable. She is hard to reach and if you can she tries to get you to go away as soon as possible. Exams are tricky and no one is allowed to ask questions. a  seems like a fun person outside of class, but was not a great professor. The topics were unorganized and she never provided clear notes. The only points come from quizzes and exams. This is by far the best class I've taken at Ohio State so far. She is extremely helpful and very funny. I recommend office hours simply because her TAs and she give very helpful hints for the exams. 4 exams. She allows an 8.5x11 page of notes for exams which is quite helpful. Posts notes online, but you need to go to lecture to understand them. This class is honestly quite easy. Dr. Van-Zandt lets you bring a cheat sheet into the exam and she even gives you extra credit for showing up to class. The exams themselves are not really that bad either and she stresses on things in lecture that usually show up in class.

Dr.  is the best professor I've had at OSU. It was a pleasure to be in his class. His tests are fair, but attending lecture is key. This man is a genius, take advantage of all of his knowledge in office hours! I would go out of my way to take another class with him.
Awesome professor - most definitely will make you interested in the brain

she does not teach students, you have to teach yourself and attend lab to learn in this class

's class was a real joy to take. Though heavy on in-depth readings each week with corresponding discussion questions, a couple of those grades are dropped so you can catch a few breaks. had great online lectures, which led to great notes, which then led to easy assignments. Only had to study twice for this class. Enjoyed her in class lectures too, even if they weren't necessary besides the attendance.

I did not enjoy her class at all because she professes her opinion more so than the actual material. She teaches from one perspective and does not really like to see any others. The class was very easy, however, there were many assignments. Many assignments could be dropped. It was half in class and half online which I preferred. Dr.  was a bit wacky at times but lectures had some important information.

Prof  seems like a nice enough person, but as an instructor she puts no work into the class. Dr. William's class was a hybrid class, meaning half online, half in-person. There were "lecture videos" given at the beginning of the week, followed by an easy quiz regarding the video. so easy
